column8: I'm not staying. Not even for him.
I'll have to be more careful.
What's life without a little pain.
You know who you're dealing with?
You. Come to fulfill my father's wishes?
Come on, Meg. Haven't we had more than enough of each other by now? Besides, I heard Sisyphus was feeling rather lonesome.
Erm... all right then, carry on, I guess.
Are you Eurydice, by any chance...? A mutual friend told me to seek you out. I've a message from Orpheus. He says he's very sorry about what happened. And believe me, I can tell he is.

Oh, you know, just out on a little stroll is all. Do me a favor, though, you see the Fury Sisters, let them know I was headed down the way I came from, will you...? Though, here, let me give you a hand.
Feeling's mutual, Sir. Someday you'll have to tell me all about how you tricked Father. I might learn a thing or two. Now here, though, let me help you up.
Up there. Contract shipment must've gotten lost.
Time to make some changes around here.
Stygius, Blade of the Underworld; I need your strength.
Aegis, Shield of Chaos; lend me your power.
Varatha, the Eternal Spear; join my pursuit.
Coronacht, the Heart-Seeker; let's deal some death.
Looks like I've a choice to make.
The gods want me to pick a favorite?
The gods want me to choose.
So that's the way it is then.
Don't spend it all in one place, mate.
Think you got me, do you?
Must be something I can use.
Don't think I've gone this far.
One of them's going to be mad.
One of them's not going to like this.

column11: We didn't make this note at the time, maybe the next line?

column8: Another day in Tartarus. Or night, I have no idea.
First, get past the wretched shades of Tartarus.
Easier said than done, and doubtless I'll be running into Meg.
The river of flame ought to be just beyond.
Find a way up to Elysium from there, and after that...
...All right, let's give it another shot.
Long way to go. Think I'm ready.
The path toward the surface lies somewhere beyond all that.
I can do this. I can do this. I can do this.
Through all that... the way to the surface...
Each exit has its own reward.
This can unlock a weapon back at home.
I can use this to unlock a weapon.
I have to pick a side.
Whichever god I don't pick won't be pleased.
Did what I had to do.
I can use that back home.
Can't get rid of me, Meg.
You touch me, and I shall have your head.
You touch me, and I shall have your head(s).
Get back in the magma and no-one gets hurt.
I wouldn't mess with me if I were you.
How many of these are there?
Whew, any more heads you'd like chopped off? No?
Sounds like Charon's breathing up ahead.
How about... a swift and painful death?
I don't know what I'm supposed to say when he gets like this...
Built to ensure no one gets out. We'll see about that.
Too bad it can't just bring me to the surface.
And not a moment too soon.
Or until I crush their bones to dust.
Say, Charon, everything all right with the old boat lately? I've not seen it around, you're just... here on your own. How did you get here, anyway?
I see, I see, makes sense, I'm glad I asked, there, mate.
At last I know the gods more than by name.
At least Zeus is helping me.
I'll find my place all right.
My place is with my mother.
We've put each other through a lot, haven't we, Meg.
I'll show you neat and orderly.
Do not mess with me right now.
This can unlock something back home.
I'll just keep this on me.
Father won't miss a couple coins.
Took a bite out of me there.
Should help me on my way.
Looks like I'm due for an upgrade.
Time to mix up my style.
That's just the edge I need.
Let's see what I can do with this sword.
Time to tune up this sword.
Now to fix up this spear.
This spear's due for a little maintenance.
This bow could use a little fine tuning.
Should get this bow back into tiptop shape.
This shield's about to get a whole lot stronger.
Should put some extra punch into this shield.
Need all the firepower I can get.
They must have lots of these upon Olympus.
Someone back home would practically die for this stuff.
Gathered Darkness... I could use that.
Five-second rule. That was five seconds right?
That ought to keep me going for a bit.
I bet Charon's going to want all this.
I'll take that as a no.
Hello to you as well, mate!
I'll just have a look around.
Fine day or night to you as well, Charon.
Truer words have not been spoken, mate.
Couldn't have said it better myself.
Oh I'm just fine thank you for asking, mate.
It's good to see you too, mate.
What's this doing all the way out here?
Is that a sight for sore eyes.
The Fates are being kind I guess.
Lord Uncle Zeus lending his support... I never thought I'd see the day. Or night. Whenever.
Looks like I caught a big one! The power of the seas should be of help.
Interested? In the power to break hearts? Sure, I don't see why not.
Yes, yes I am. Let's break some hearts.
I sure could use some company now that she mentions it. The power of the hunt sounds handy too!
With your power, Lord Ares, maybe I'll get out of here yet.
You know, that sounds fantastic right about now. Pleasure to make your acquaintance, Dionysus mate.
Let's make some waves, right, Uncle?
Coin goes in, that comes out.
Well, Father? I'm trespassing through your secret hall, and going up.
I'll just be a moment, Father.
Let's see what's up for sale.
They got me. No way to patch up. Got to keep going.
I'm hurt. Can't heal myself. But I can fight.
Nngh, what I wouldn't give for, say, a healing flask of some sort.
Wonder where I can use this.
This needs more keys to open.
That's going to take more keys.
How many have I got now?
Won't bother asking how come all my keepsakes are here.
Maybe I should switch things up.
Tartarus... I won't be stuck here all my life.
Just need to get from here across all that.
I've gone farther than I can see from here.
The chambers of Tartarus have probably all rearranged themselves by now.
I'm going to get through all this.
And I can reckon quite a bit.
Way to spoil the surprise, old man.
I do enjoy dead people's fineries.
You feeling lucky, too, old man? Then show yourself! No...?
Lots of wretchedness to go around, I guess.
It wasn't all that hard to find really.
I'd best take all the evidence I find.
You kill me, I kill you.
Wretches of the damned, beware. I'm coming back.
Tartarus... strong enough to seal away the Titans. But not me.
Fine day or whenever to get me out of here.
I won't back down. Not now or ever.
I know you're out there, Mother.
This won't end well for you.
I'll have to withstand the whims of Chaos to extract the benefits a few chambers from now.
My Boon from Chaos has transformed.
The Boon I got from Chaos has a new effect.
My Chaos Boon switched to a new effect.
A curse of Chaos has been lifted.
A curse of Chaos has expired.
My Chaos Boon evolved a new effect.
My Boon from Master Chaos has evolved.
It's the blood of the Underworld...
Should save my coin for something I need.
They won't so much as scratch me.
I so do like a challenge.
Just you try and hit me.
Let's see if I've still got it.
They won't harm a hair on my head.
I'll gain more Darkness with this.
Should help me gain more Darkness.
Don't let it go to your head?
Until next time, gigantic gorgon head.
Ow I shouldn't have done that.
Uff should not have done that!
All I got was that stupid onion.
Father's famous sense of humor shining through again.
I don't like it, but I'll eat it.
An onion. Instead of... whatever I was supposed to get. Ugh.
At least they peeled it for me.
Leave it to the god of wine to liven things up around here.
Not what I need right now.
The Fates aren't listening to me.
My authority does have its limitations.
Exagryph, the Adamant Rail; come turn my foes to ash.
Exagryph, the Rail of Adamant; annihilate all who oppose me.
Some modifications to the rail are in order.
Let's see how we can modify the rail.
A blade fit for a god.
They'll fear me with this spear.
I need a higher Pain Level with the Pact of Punishment to go in this.
I need to power up the Pact of Punishment back home to go in this.
My Pain Level isn't high enough.
I need a higher Pain Level to go in.
My Pain Level's too low to get in.
Need a higher Pain Level to go in there.
Not getting in without a higher Pain Level.
Not authorized to go in there.
The Pact back home's the key to getting into this.
My keepsake from Chaos will protect me.
Let's pay Chaos a visit then.
Got here as fast as I could.
I'll get you for last time.
I see you grew your heads back.
Bone Hydra! It's been too long.
I will keep coming back just like your stupid heads.
Don't you have something to say to me?
We're both immortals, Meg. We'll be seeing plenty of each other for a while yet. And honestly I've come to welcome these occasions, yes.
You sure about this, Meg? What's with the change of heart?
Oh, you'll soon find that it's the real thing, Meg. And as for how I got it, well, I know a guy. Maybe I'll introduce you at some point?
Think I know what you're going to say.
I don't like her very much.
That's one way to prove I'm innocent.
Hope she won't be back anytime soon.
All right, then, let's get mad.
Is this where Father's goons assemble to come after me?
Too bad I can't just take the ferry to the surface.
I'll be the judge of that.
I'll leave my mark all right.
Who's ready for the real afterlife experience?
I take some pride in making messes, yes.
How about I take a closer look.
You don't need me, and I don't need you.
If only you could see me now, Father.
Time for another blood spree, then.
I think I'm going to Elysium.
Not in the mood for your jesting, Father.
What are you, the Three Fates?
You really need to turn down the heat in that place.
Got a feeling it's Tisiphone this time.
This what the outside world is like...?
Champions of Elysium, I have returned.
Another day or night in paradise.
I get the feeling I am being watched.
Took care of those for you, mate.
No need to thank me, mate.
No urns permitted in this chamber.
That was as fast as I've gone.
Quick as a flash that time.
I'll have to give them new pains to recall.
Is this really as good as it gets for mortalkind?
Cheers for the vote of confidence, old man.
This place is near as gloomy as the House.
Just checking up on you, sir.
...I... will mention if I see him, sir.
Just bide your time here, sir.
I am most grateful to you, sir.
You don't attack me indiscriminately, I give you Ambrosia. I don't think I'm being over-generous!
I beat the Bull of Minos.
I guess I win this round.
Who's the short one now, huh?!
That ought to shut him up.
They say to never meet your heroes.
Can I get some applause or something here?
Hope you enjoyed the show out in the stands!
I guess I win this round.
To my health! Although I'm full.
Too bad I can't bottle this stuff.
No getting out without a drink.
I'm healthy as can be, but cheers!
Who makes door locks connected to a fountain?
Got to use the fountain to get out of here.
Sure has a lot of these.
I can switch to a different Boon.
I'm sure Lady Athena won't mind.
I'm sure Lord Uncle Zeus won't mind.
Lord Uncle Zeus won't mind, will he?
A generous offer, Lord Uncle Zeus.
I can't say no, Lord Zeus.
I'm sure Uncle Poseidon won't mind.
You drive a hard bargain, Uncle.
I'm sure Lord Ares won't mind.
I'm sure Lady Aphrodite won't mind.
Lady Aphrodite, how can I say no?
I'm sure Lady Artemis won't mind.
I'm sure Lord Dionysus won't mind.
This Boon should serve me better.
A better Boon for the circumstances.
A change of Boons was in order.
Too good an offer to pass up.
Playing me against each other, aren't they.
I can't say no to that.
I promise I'm not playing favorites here.
Appreciate the lift, Lord Hermes sir. Now let's go!
Time to pick up the pace.
Lord Hermes, I am in your debt.
Err I'm sorry mate, I meant you no offense.
I'll... keep it to myself for now, then. Thanks.
Say hi to Hermes for me!
Tell Hermes I said hi, will you?
The mother of all Soul Catchers.
It's that big Soul Catcher again.
I'll keep my soul for now, thanks.
Farewell for now, sinister ball of butterflies.
Butterflies better stay away from me.
You know nothing of my struggles.
I'll be the judge of that.
It's more of a brisk jog.
Perhaps your expectations are too high.
I pray his ego will recover soon.
No, but you're going to anyway.
You leave Cerberus out of this.
Mind asking him to tone it down a bit?
What would you know of it?
Then I'll deal with you same as all the rest.
Not much I can do with this now.
No coin left in this pool.
What's with the air up here.
Hope it's nicer outside than it is in here.
Need to keep looking down those passageways.
Got to find something for Cerberus.
Now for a chat with Cerberus.
Good! Now I just need to head off the beaten path here and see what I can find.
You know how many Satyrs I had to get through to bring you this, boy? So could you let me through?
Break time, boy! Got you a veritable feast, here, in this lovely sack.
One Satyr Sack for one good boy.
Hey boy, got you something you are going to eat right up!
Got this delicious sack of meal for you, boy.
One Satyr Sack coming right up!
Please enjoy the finest dining, courtesy of our ongoing Satyr infestation here.
I can leave, or I can keep exploring the west.
Should I go fight some Satyrs, or get out of here?
Maybe I should check the other passageways before I leave.
Could check the other passageways before I go.
A Satyr Sack for my boy Cerberus.
Cerberus just loves... whatever this stuff is.
A whole entire sack of something!
A sack fit for a huge three-headed hound.
Just what I need, a foul sack!
Just the foul sack I need.
Cerberus can never get enough of this stuff.
That's quite a stash there, Charon!
Should stock up for the road ahead.
Father must have put you up to this.
Working on getting you your treat still, boy.
Not going to budge, are you?
Cerberus puts up with so much.
You wouldn't fight me, would you?
Won't even lift a paw, will you.
I ought to be ashamed of myself.
I guess there's only one thing left to do. Isn't that so, Father?
I don't think I'll ever get accustomed to the breeze.
One last bit of business to take care of, then.
My mother. Persephone. Why did she leave? Why did she leave you? Why did she leave me?
In the name of someone very sore right now.
No. You're going home, not me.
The wrath of Poseidon at my beck and call.
He loves to eat. Can you blame him?
I can do this. I can do this.
Say hi to Hypnos for me.
I thought you planned to handle this yourself!
Why don't you tell your loyal subjects to stay out of this!
Upon my name, I'll bury all you wretches here and now!
Hope this can get me out of here.
Should be able to get back through here.
Let's just go down this Satyr hole.
Oh you'll think better of me soon!
And I am shocked to hear it!
And I think you're a miserable failure as a father!
It's my time to do with as I please!
I don't care what you think!
Oh this isn't a waste of time at all!
It beats having to live within your House!
Would that you could shut up and fight!
Liar! Why should I trust a single word you say?
No! She's out there. I know it!
I can leave, or explore more tunnels.
Cerberus is back on duty. Got to find him something to eat.
There's Cerberus. Won't budge till I find him a treat.
Time to find old Cerberus a Satyr sack.
Won't get out of here until I find something for Cerberus.
Cerberus guarding the gates as always.
Time to clear some Satyr tunnels and get out of here.
Now to get Cerberus to step aside.
Want something to eat, boy? Huh?
You hungry, Cerberus? I bet you are!
If you beat me, I'll just keep coming back!
You know you're tresspassing on private property!
What are you doing to this place?
Look what you've done to this place!
Haven't you learned your lesson yet?
Has to be the last of this lot.
How many more of these are there.
Must be the last of them.
If I were a Satyr sack, where would I be...
I'll send your wretches back where they belong!
Why don't you let your wretches rest in peace?
Then I'll just have to attend to them!
Not interested in the analysis now, Father!
You know exactly what it's going to take!
It'll take you getting out of my blasted way!
I'll have you join them soon!
Am I brutish or am I holding back? Make up your blasted mind!
You want me to go all out? Then fine!
I said shut up with the analysis!
I need you to quit blathering and fight!
And you cannot treat me this way!
Just have to cross a couple rivers, then.
Think I'll go where it suits me.
Not poisoned at the moment, thanks.

No, no, no, of course, and, thanks for your directness about this. Look I know you've been through a lot with Orpheus, but... it's clear to me how much you love each other, still. I'm just glad we met.
Never enough of these back at the House.
Should fetch me something good back home.
Stygius shuddered as I picked it up...
Coronacht shuddered when I picked this up...
My weapon shuddered at the touch of it...
My weapons can grow even stronger now.
This can unlock a hidden aspect of my weapons.
Who should I give this to...
Hope I didn't keep you waiting, ladies.
Erm, this is not the deadly Hydra chamber I expected.
Bone Hydra! I love what you've done with the place!
I see you re-grew your neck!
How's the old neck holding up?
You and me, Severed Hydra Head!
Hydra heads were never meant to fly.
Back to wherever your neck went.
Some of those urns have coin in them don't they.
These urns have coin in them.
Why do these vermin carry coin?
I got to hurry it up...
I need to purge a Boon to get out of here.
I have to use the Purging Pool back there.
I need to purge one of my Boons first.
Underworld Customs, got to purge a Boon.
Urgh forgot to purge a Boon.
Have to give up one of my Boons first.
All right, lads, let's see who makes the bigger waves.
Hello, Wave-Makers! I, too, can make waves.
Must be the work of Daedalus.
Come forth and be swatted, deadly butterflies.
There you are, gigantic Soul Catcher.
Time for another voyage 'board the Barge of Death.
The Barge of Death is always here for me.
Have to say, the Barge of Death is never late.
Ready when you are, Barge of Death.
Why it's the Barge of Death.
Somebody lose a spine out there?
Lovely place to have to smash my way through.
Lots of Exalted Shades between me and the exit.
Asterius and Theseus are probably expecting me.
Just need to storm my way through that eternal paradise.
You know, if I was permanently dead maybe I wouldn't mind all this.
For all his faults, Father did make this place look good.
Did Daedalus himself build all of this...?
Just what I've been looking for.
It's called a smile, Meg. I'm simply pleased to see you, nothing more. It could have been one of your sisters, no offense.
...This has to be some kind of bad dream.
Theseus, before you flap your ghostly gums at me again, I'd like to hear from good Asterius this time! He almost never gets a word in thanks to you.
Made some arrangements to ensure your chamber here got some more visibility is all. Made for a good excuse to visit you again, sir!
I thought you'd like it, sir. Almost a shame we seldom get such imports from Olympus around here. I hope I can appreciate it for myself sometime. Once all this is over with, I think.
It is all right. Thanks, Than.
That is an ominous-looking portal on the ground right there.
What is that portal thing there on the ground?
So all I need to do is sacrifice some of my life essence to go in here?
That looks like a Daedalus Hammer!
Daedalus, wherever you may be right now, thank you.
Another one of those gigantic Satyrs?
Go clop your hooves in hell.
That's the most gigantic vermin I have ever seen.
Another one of those especially gigantic vermin!
What sort of terrible Snakestone is that?
It's that giant Snakestone once again!
The Satyrs must be fashioning those things...
Don't like the look of that big Bother over there.
That blasted giant Bother has come back.
Time to deal with Father's pest problem I guess.
One of their disgusting lairs, huh.
Can't quite get acclimated to this smell.
And Father thinks my chambers are a mess!
Or I'll slay you instead if you prefer!
Lesson one: Don't mess with either one of us!
No doubt at all from me.
This gigantic vermin head deserves a lot more credit if you ask me.
Must be the Fountain Chamber I commissioned back at home...
Ah good, this has to be the chamber renovation I put in.
Glad I put in the order for a Fountain Chamber in this area.
That must be one of those Infernal Troves!
My Keepsake Collection! Just what the House Contractor ordered.
That Darkness there felt different than before.
That key, it granted me Fated Authority.
Gemstones, and a little extra for Charon.
That Nectar also amplified one of my Boons.
Don't think that's going to work!
You sure you won't assist me here, Meg?
I can't do that right now!
Achilles might know what to do with this.
This holds some sort of power, but for what?
That a genuine Ambrosia bottle there?
Huh, I can't seem to open it...
Must be something I can do with this.
Last time I felt a cold like this was... on the surface, but, who...? Well, one way to find out, then, in the name of Hades! Olympus! I accept this message!
Are all the seasons on the surface freezing cold?
I've the power of the freezing surface, now.
I'm in your debt, great Goddess Demeter.
I'm sure that Demeter won't mind.
Lady Demeter won't mind, will she?
I can't refuse this, Lady Demeter.
Good Lady Demeter, I must accept.
Wait... Persephone... Mother... is Demeter's daughter?
Winter... that's when it's cold, or something, right?
Could dash clear through that wall I think...
Wasn't this whole expanse once lush and green?
The Bloodless lie in wait out there I guess.
It's nice and warm out here, I'll give it that.
Just a few rides across the Phlegethon, and up we go.
That blasted Hydra must be back by now.
This place has definitely seen better days.
This place has definitely seen better days. Or nights?
Thanks for believing in me, my good Shade!
I dedicate this victory to you, good Shade!
That shade there, have I got a fan?
I won again, Shade, thanks to your support!
How does Daedalus come up with this stuff?
I know you're out there, fish.
What do you know, a Hellfish.
That's one more fish for me!
I'll get you next time, fish!
Bone Hydra, you're back! How wonderful.
Hydra, I feel like we're just not getting through to one another, here.
Bone Hydra, how come we never talk?
Bone Hydra, if you understand me, menacingly hiss.
Bone Hydra, I hope you know this isn't personal, don't you?
Bone Hydra... can I call you Bone Hydra? Lernie, maybe? Lernie, I like that.
You don't mind if I call you Lernie from now on, right?
I'll take that as a 'No, not at all, thank you for asking, friend.'
Why, hello, Lernie, what have you been up to since I last destroyed your multitude of heads?
Good day, Lernie, and now? Prepare to die.
How goes it lately, Lernie, everything just fine?
I'm back, Lernie, to kill you once again!
If only you knew just how I feel, Lernie.
I know you missed me, Lernie, and I missed you, too!
Lernie, wonderful to see you once again!
What's the matter, Lernie? You seem quite upset!
How is the magma temperature lately, Lernie?
Lernie, if you'd like for me to kill you, hiss.
Lernie, hiss once if you think you're going to lose.
Lovely chatting with you, Lernie dear!
Could use the Rod of Fishing there.
Hey think I see a fish.
Got to hold nice and still.
What lurks in the River Styx?
Hard to see in all that red.
What lurks in the River Phlegethon?
I'll save you from the magma, fishes.
What lurks in the River Lethe?
What lurks in this surface river here?
What lurks in the waters of the surface?
What lurks in the waters of chaos?
Fish swimming in primordial ooze, my favorite.
Well, Guan Yu...? Take good care of Varatha for me.
Malphon, the Twin Fists; what say we crack some skulls.
Twin Fists of Malphon; our strength combined surely cannot be stopped.
Let's punch things up a bit.
New styles for the Twin Fists.
Time to fix up these Fists.
These Fists are hungry to fight.
These Fists are going to do the talking, soon.
We made it, Stygius. I hope this Arthur serves you well someday.
We're here, Coronacht. May you serve Rama well... if you haven't already done so, I guess...
Let's see how quickly I can slay you all.
I'm sure you'll think of something soon enough.
Headed over to Elysium right now...
Not afraid of you or your damn spear.
Guess I'll see what I can do about it, Father.
All right, let's catch some fish.
That was for you, good Shade!
Hope you enjoyed the show, my good Shade!
Thank you for your support, my Shade!
We got them, my good Shade!
Showed them who's boss, didn't we, Shade?
Was not about to let you down, my Shade!
Makes up for last time I hope, my good Shade?
Oh, haha! It's just a tiny vermin!
I much prefer gigantic vermin, thanks...
You don't scare me, tiny vermin!
No, anything but the tiny vermin...!
I see you drawn in the arms of the seventh avatar...
This is the greatest delicacy of Olympus, Master Chaos. It's for you. I think normally it would be difficult for the Olympians to get it to you here.
I'd like to see more options.
The Fates say no I guess.
I guess the Fates won't let me try that here.
Where do you think you're going?
Pick on somebody your own size next time!
I suppose I'm somewhat infamous around here now. Though, you can call me Zagreus, or stranger, whatever suits you.
I'm glad you did, though, Than.
Why, Lernie, you are looking positively fabulous, I have to say.
Lernie, you really didn't have to reconstitute yourself just for my sake.
Stopped anybody from attempting to leave Asphodel of late, Lernie?
We'll have to catch up some other time, Lernie, as I'm in a bit of a rush.
Not really in a talking mood this time, Lernie.
All right, Lernie, let's have it out between us, then.
Why must we always fight like this, Lernie?
I have longed to hear the sound of your hiss, Lernie.
Get you for last time, Father.
I'm leaving, Father. Try and stop me.
Think I missed my chance here.
Don't think I'll get a bite at this rate.
No river denizens about I think.
Have to take care of that Butterfly Ball!
Need to deal with the blasted Butterfly Ball!
They'll just keep coming 'cause of that Butterfly Ball!
I should deal with that Butterfly Ball!
There's no end to these guys!
I'll get right on it, Than!
I say: Sure, Than, sounds good to me.
I'll be as reckless as I want!
I see you stand your ground against the serpent's flame...
I see your prideful fall down from the heavens to the flames...
Beyond the frozen overlook... await the first glimpse of the sun to your left... then onward through the cold.
Beyond the frozen overlook... await the first glimpse of the sun to your left... then onward through the cold.
Wha, that thing, that's... the sun...
So much water... Uncle Poseidon's realm.
